# Angular + PrimeNG

- Standalone components only
- PrimeNG over custom UI; custom HTML only when PrimeNG has no fit
- **PrimeNG 21 in this repo** — use [primeng.org](https://primeng.org) docs and DOM class names for v21 only (`p-menu-item-*`, not `p-menuitem-*`)
- Before custom CSS or config against PrimeNG internals, check the installed version’s docs (CSS Classes / API tables)
- **Theme preset: Lara** (`definePreset(Lara, …)` in `pip-preset.ts`) — locked; do not change base preset without explicit user approval
- No new abstractions (services, base classes, shared wrappers) without explicit ask
- Section components receive data via `@Input()` from dashboard parent
- Use flex containers around components to dictate shape and responsiveness relative to other components
